## Instructions

### Branch Naming Convention

All branches must follow the project ticket pattern:

```
{{conventions.branch_pattern}}
```

### Creating a New Branch

```bash
git checkout {{conventions.default_branch}}
git pull origin {{conventions.default_branch}}
git checkout -b {{conventions.branch_pattern}}
git push -u origin {{conventions.branch_pattern}}
```

### Commit Message Format

Follow [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/):

```
<type>(<scope>): <subject>

<body>

Closes {{conventions.branch_pattern}}
```

**Types**:
| Type | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `feat` | New feature |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `docs` | Documentation only |
| `style` | Formatting, no code change |
| `refactor` | Code restructuring |
| `test` | Adding/updating tests |
| `chore` | Build, CI, dependencies |

**Scope**: Component or area affected

### Pull Request Workflow

**Creating a PR with GitHub CLI**:
```bash
# Create PR
gh pr create --title "{{conventions.branch_pattern}}: Feature description" \
  --base {{conventions.default_branch}}

# Create draft PR
gh pr create --draft --title "{{conventions.branch_pattern}}: WIP Feature"

# Request review
gh pr edit --add-reviewer username1,username2
```

**PR Title Format**:
```
{{conventions.branch_pattern}}: Brief description of change
```

### Merging Strategy

Use **squash merging** for feature branches:

```bash
gh pr merge --squash --delete-branch
```

### Keeping Branch Updated

```bash
# Merge strategy
git checkout {{conventions.default_branch}}
git pull origin {{conventions.default_branch}}
git checkout -
git merge {{conventions.default_branch}}

# Rebase strategy
git fetch origin
git rebase origin/{{conventions.default_branch}}
```

### Cleanup After Merge

```bash
# Delete local merged branches
git branch --merged {{conventions.default_branch}} | grep -v "{{conventions.default_branch}}" | xargs git branch -d

# Prune remote tracking branches
git fetch --prune
```

### Useful GitHub CLI Commands

```bash
# List open PRs
gh pr list

# Check PR status and CI checks
gh pr status
gh pr checks

# View PR diff
gh pr diff

# Approve PR
gh pr review --approve

# Request changes
gh pr review --request-changes --body "Changes needed..."
```
